entries.femaleVariant: Dear viewers, thank you for tuning in. I'm Arif Iqbal, and this is WNS News.
We have a breaking story. It appears that, during the attack on Konpeki Plaza, longtime Arasaka CEO Saburo Arasaka was killed.
The assassins managed to escape, but it is no mystery who sent them.
The Arvin Accord, signed by President Myers, required all parties of the conflict to renounce all shows of force.
On behalf of the entire WNS News team, we offer our sincerest condolences to the Arasaka family as they mourn their loss.
The family's suffering must be immense. You have our deepest sympathies.
This shocking development comes to us directly from his son, Yorinobu Arasaka.
Despite many provocations, Arasaka has honored these agreements. Our rivals hold no such honor.
And they will soon gravely regret those unforgivable actions.
